Kenya - Second Structural Adjustment
            Operation Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The loan and credit would support a
            program of action agreed upon with the Government involving
            measures to rationalize the trade regime, promote exports,
            stimulate agricultural output, encourage conservation and
            efficient production of energy and reduce population growth.
            The program is described in the Government's Letter of
            Development Policy to the Bank and Association. Foreign
            exchange would be used for essential imports. Counterpart
            funds would be used for development-related expenditures in
            the Central Government's budget.
